<definition id="fs-idp54272512"><term>photosynthesis</term><meaning id="fs-idp197718640"> process whereby light energy promotes the reaction of water and carbon dioxide to form carbohydrates and oxygen; this allows photosynthetic organisms to store energy</meaning></definition>
